body:
I'm no expert, but this code [link](https://github.com/SFML/SFML/blob/master/src/SFML/Window/Win32/WindowImplWin32.cpp#L986) seems to me a bit over-complicated and may fire many unnecessary events while the devices are being initialised 

Wouldn't this be enough?
```
case WM_DEVICECHANGE:
{
    if (wParam == DBT_DEVNODES_CHANGED) JoystickImpl::updateConnections();
    break;
}
```

It works fine on my end, 3 calls for my 3 devices, and it reacts on the port changes. USB 3.0 lag is still present.
